    "the set of linear maps from V to itself.",
    "In order for it to be a representation, the map ρ needs to satisfy the following additional conditions ρ g ρ g ′ = ρ g g ′,ρ 1 = 1, (B.2)for all g, g ′ ∈ G (0).",
    "Let us phrase the above in an alternative way, which opens up the generalization to higherrepresentations.",
